One notable trend in the CNS stimulants market is the increasing emphasis on personalized medicine. By leveraging advancements in technology and understanding the genetic factors influencing drug response, companies are moving towards tailoring treatments to individual patients. This personalized approach not only enhances the effectiveness of CNS stimulants but also helps in minimizing adverse effects, thereby improving patient outcomes.

The market for CNS stimulants is also witnessing a shift towards online pharmacies as a popular distribution channel. With the growing trend of e-commerce and digital health, online pharmacies offer a convenient option for patients to access their medications from the comfort of their homes. This trend is expected to further drive market growth by providing easier access to CNS stimulants for patients in remote areas or those with mobility constraints.

